WEBVTT

00:02.960 --> 00:04.951
[Vehicles passing ]

00:17.670 --> 00:19.285
Caramel.
Mm-hmm.

00:19.290 --> 00:20.575
Hints of black currant.

00:20.580 --> 00:24.209
Rsmn
but has an earthy finish.

00:24.210 --> 00:25.575
I'm going with Ethiopian.

00:25.580 --> 00:27.036
Ha! Kenyan.

00:27.040 --> 00:28.246
Oh.
[ Laughs ]

00:28.250 --> 00:30.536
It's close. Close.

00:30.540 --> 00:32.531
[ Pounding ]
Woman: Hey!

00:32.540 --> 00:34.576
Sounds like somebody's getting
a little nervous back there.

00:34.580 --> 00:36.491
Hey!
Let me out of here!
[ Chuckles ]

00:36.500 --> 00:37.535
[ Car hits bump ]

00:37.540 --> 00:39.030
[ Tape deck whirs ]

00:39.040 --> 00:40.826
[ Neil Diamond's
"Sweet Caroline" plays ]

00:40.830 --> 00:43.162
[ Buttons clicking ]

00:43.170 --> 00:45.070
It's not ejecting.
It's stuck.

00:45.080 --> 00:46.411
Oh, this stupid tape deck.

00:46.420 --> 00:48.206
It's stuck.
Who cares?

00:48.210 --> 00:49.495
The hell?

00:52.960 --> 00:56.612
Where it began

00:56.620 --> 01:00.454
I can't begin to knowin'
[ Humming ]

01:00.460 --> 01:04.282
_ But then I know
It's growmg strong

01:07.830 --> 01:11.948
Both: Was in the spring

01:11.960 --> 01:15.703
Then spring became
the summer

01:15.710 --> 01:22.206
Who'd have believed
you'd come along?

01:22.210 --> 01:23.700
Hands

01:23.710 --> 01:24.324
[ Fire extinguisher hisses ]

01:24.330 --> 01:26.457
[ Coughs ]

01:26.460 --> 01:28.451
Touching hands
Open the window, man!

01:28.460 --> 01:29.609
[ Coughing ]

01:29.620 --> 01:30.609
[ Car horn blares ]

01:30.620 --> 01:31.996
Reaching out

01:32.000 --> 01:33.206
[ Grunts ]

01:33.210 --> 01:35.246
[ Grunting ]
Touching me

01:35.250 --> 01:36.319
[Tires squeal ]

01:36.330 --> 01:38.878
Touching you

01:38.880 --> 01:40.700
[ Screams ]

01:40.710 --> 01:43.452
Sweet Caroline

01:43.460 --> 01:45.917
[ Car horn blares ]

01:45.920 --> 01:47.410
Good times
never seemed so good

01:47.420 --> 01:49.069
[ Glass shatters ]

01:49.080 --> 01:50.456
[Tires screech ]

01:50.460 --> 01:52.030
[ Car horn blares ]

01:52.040 --> 01:54.167
I've been inclined

01:54.170 --> 01:55.376
[ Screams ]

01:55.380 --> 01:56.495
[Tires screech ]

01:56.500 --> 02:00.072
Hold on.
To believe there never would

02:00.080 --> 02:01.206
Car!

02:01.210 --> 02:03.110
[ Screaming ]
[ Car horn blares ]

02:03.120 --> 02:06.032
Sweet Caroline

02:06.040 --> 02:07.530
[Tires squeal ]

02:07.540 --> 02:12.034
[ Screams ]
Good times never
seemed so good

02:20.790 --> 02:22.701
[ Slot machines beeping,
indistinct talking ]

02:25.120 --> 02:27.668
Nervous habit?
[ Clears throat ]
Hmm?

02:27.670 --> 02:29.206
The label.
Oh.

02:29.210 --> 02:31.826
Nah, just a regular one.

02:31.830 --> 02:32.990
You from around here?

02:33.000 --> 02:35.616
Mmmhmm.
Born and raised.

02:35.620 --> 02:36.871
You?
Michigan.

02:36.880 --> 02:40.031
Okay.
Yeah, just in for a meeting.

02:40.040 --> 02:41.871
Fly out at the crack
of dawn tomorrow.

02:41.880 --> 02:44.917
Out too late
[chuckles] up too early.

02:44.920 --> 02:46.740
I think my body clock
got broken

02:46.750 --> 02:47.819
in my third tour
of the 'Stan.

02:49.790 --> 02:51.576
Oh, Afghanistan.
[ Chuckles ]

02:51.580 --> 02:53.992
Explains the, uh, dog tags.

02:54.000 --> 02:56.742
Yeah, saw a lot of crazy stuff
over there, but, uh --

02:56.750 --> 02:59.708
Oh, really?
Yeah.

02:59.710 --> 03:00.745
You know
what you never forget?

03:00.750 --> 03:01.990
What?

03:02.000 --> 03:04.821
Your first firefight.
Hmm.

03:04.830 --> 03:08.379
Chaos, the noise, the blood.
It's...

03:08.380 --> 03:10.666
Bull?

03:10.670 --> 03:13.161
Hmm?
Well, you know
what they say in Pashto --

03:13.170 --> 03:15.957
"He who spreads his own goat
dung is bound to step in it."

03:15.960 --> 03:17.871
Pash".
...to. Yeah.

03:17.880 --> 03:19.780
It's what they speak.
In the 'Stan.

03:19.790 --> 03:21.326
Yeah.
Yeah.

03:21.330 --> 03:23.662
Anyone who actually served there
would know that, so...

03:23.670 --> 03:26.787
Your dog tags don't match
the name on your credit card,

03:26.790 --> 03:28.246
and nothing about your car keys
says "rental,"

03:28.250 --> 03:31.037
so I'm guessing you're
not in from out of town, either?

03:31.040 --> 03:33.998
I know you asked
ifI was from around here,

03:34.000 --> 03:36.161
figuring we could
go back to my place probably

03:36.170 --> 03:37.819
because there's a woman
back at yours.

03:37.830 --> 03:39.036
Am I right?
Uh...

03:39.040 --> 03:41.076
Hesitation --
it's when your body says "yes"

03:41.080 --> 03:42.490
before your mouth
can say "no."

03:42.500 --> 03:44.491
I.e., until you get
your lie straight,

03:44.500 --> 03:46.411
I'm pretty sure only one of us
is getting luclq tonight.

03:48.880 --> 03:51.451
Thanks, sweetheart.
Cheers.

03:51.460 --> 03:52.870
Y-Yeah.

03:52.880 --> 03:54.245
[ Crowd cheering ]
Dealer: Snake eyes.

03:54.250 --> 03:57.071
Yes! Okay, that's water
and power, folks.

03:57.080 --> 03:58.957
Now we play
for beer and cable.

03:58.960 --> 04:00.530
You, uh, sure you want
to do that, honey?

04:00.540 --> 04:03.031
Oh, gosh,
maybe you're right, toots.

04:03.040 --> 04:06.168
I'm feeling luclq tonight.
Okay.

04:06.170 --> 04:07.956
Gimme eight, gimme eight, eight,
eight, eight, eight!

04:12.000 --> 04:13.410
Seven. Seven out.
[ Crowd groans ]

04:13.420 --> 04:15.035
Blinds away.

04:17.500 --> 04:19.070
[ Chuckles lightly ]

04:21.210 --> 04:22.245
Um...

04:22.250 --> 04:24.320
You know why you're such
a bad gambler?

04:24.330 --> 04:25.661
Because your dice
are loaded?

04:25.670 --> 04:27.206
Because you don't know
when to quit.

04:27.210 --> 04:28.746
Mm.

04:28.750 --> 04:30.320
Boss wants a word.

04:32.120 --> 04:34.031
Sue Lynn, c'mon,
how about a marker?

04:34.040 --> 04:35.246
Just a measly two K.

04:35.250 --> 04:36.820
You already owe us 11.

04:36.830 --> 04:39.207
And you just blew
your military disability check

04:39.210 --> 04:40.245
at the craps table.

04:40.250 --> 04:42.377
I'll get you your money,
okay?

04:42.380 --> 04:45.577
You_don't have to...
knit me a noose.

04:45.580 --> 04:46.956
This_isn't
a collections call.

04:48.170 --> 04:50.240
My rather rebellious
granddaughter

04:50.250 --> 04:51.410
has run away again.

04:51.420 --> 04:53.615
Nina? Well, just
cancel her credit cards.

04:53.620 --> 04:55.326
She'll be back in an hour.

04:55.330 --> 04:57.742
She left three days ago
without her cards or her car,

04:57.750 --> 04:58.956
and she's not answering
her phone.

04:58.960 --> 05:00.450
Okay, well,
did you call the police?

05:00.460 --> 05:02.280
I don't trust the police.

05:02.290 --> 05:04.030
We prefer to keep them
out of our business.

05:04.040 --> 05:05.371
How is this my problem?

05:05.380 --> 05:06.995
You're gonna
bring Nina back.

05:07.000 --> 05:08.570
[ Chuckles ] Wha--

05:10.120 --> 05:11.610
Sounds like his job.

05:11.620 --> 05:13.952
We've been searching day
and night, trying to find her.

05:13.960 --> 05:15.200
And you think
I can do better?

05:15.210 --> 05:16.996
Isn't that why
they gave you a medal?

05:17.000 --> 05:19.571
For finding people?
Those were enemy combatants.

05:19.580 --> 05:21.411
In Afghanistan.

05:21.420 --> 05:23.115
It's a slight difference.

05:23.120 --> 05:24.781
I'd think
you'd want to help.

05:24.790 --> 05:26.496
Given how close
you were to Benny.

05:35.380 --> 05:38.372
Ah.
Still bitter.

05:38.380 --> 05:40.416
Nah, I'm just mystified.

05:40.420 --> 05:42.411
So, I wasn't good enough
for your son,

05:42.420 --> 05:44.115
but now I'm good enough
to track down his daughter?

05:44.120 --> 05:46.782
Is that your thinking?
Oh, I can think of 11,000
other reasons.

05:46.790 --> 05:48.417
Intimidation.
How un-you.

05:48.420 --> 05:50.240
She's my only grandchild!

05:53.290 --> 05:56.703
It's not easy for me,
coming to you.

05:56.710 --> 05:58.280
I need someone I can trust.

06:01.540 --> 06:02.916
Well, war ended
for me 12 years ago.

06:02.920 --> 06:04.035
I'm not up to it, okay?

06:05.380 --> 06:06.495
I'm sorry.

06:08.580 --> 06:10.992
[ Door opens ]

06:11.000 --> 06:14.618
The heat of the night

06:14.620 --> 06:16.997
It's gone so cold

06:17.000 --> 06:18.115
Yeah

06:18.120 --> 06:19.326
[ Music stops ]

06:19.330 --> 06:21.116
[ Insects chirping ]

06:24.170 --> 06:25.910
[TV playing indistinctly ]

06:27.960 --> 06:29.825
Hey, sis.
Ooh!

06:29.830 --> 06:31.377
I said not in the house,
okay?

06:31.380 --> 06:33.701
Wanna play?
No. It's past midnight.

06:33.710 --> 06:34.825
You need to go to bed.

06:34.830 --> 06:38.038
I wanted to see
how much you lost.

06:38.040 --> 06:41.498
Punk. Well, at least
I got a job offer.

06:41.500 --> 06:43.161
Now we both have jobs.

06:43.170 --> 06:44.956
Well, I didn't say
I was gonna take it.

06:44.960 --> 06:46.951
You know, I know we need
the money, but...

06:49.330 --> 06:52.037
Okay, come on, it's late.
You know the drill.

06:53.500 --> 06:58.119
I, Ansel, future midfield menace
for the Portland Timbers,

06:58.120 --> 07:02.204
hereby promise
to brush and floss --

07:02.210 --> 07:03.495
And not to go to bed
with your boots on.

07:03.500 --> 07:05.491
I swear.
Okay, go. Bedslq.

07:07.710 --> 07:10.417
Dex,
are we gonna be okay?

07:11.790 --> 07:14.076
Yeah.

07:14.080 --> 07:16.822
Yeah, buddy,
we're gonna be okay.

07:16.830 --> 07:18.912
Go get some sleep,
alright?

07:24.080 --> 07:25.115
[ Sighs ]

07:34.120 --> 07:36.532
[ Cellphone ringing ]
[ Exhales sharply]

07:36.540 --> 07:39.498
This is Hollis.
Hey, it's Dex.

07:39.500 --> 07:41.821
Yeah, clear my debt,
get me a grand for expenses

07:41.830 --> 07:43.786
and a list of Nina's friends,
and I'll do it.

07:43.790 --> 07:45.701
I'll tell Sue Lynn.

07:45.710 --> 07:47.325
[ Cellphone clicks ]

07:52.880 --> 07:55.747
So let me get this straight --
Sue Lynn ruins your life,

07:55.750 --> 07:58.822
and now you're gonna bring home
her spoiled, brat granddaughter?

07:58.830 --> 08:01.287
It's not Nina's fault she grew
up with bad role models.

08:01.290 --> 08:03.281
I'd just be careful
turning over old stones.

08:03.290 --> 08:04.609
Don't you have an opening
to worry about?

08:04.620 --> 08:07.498
I do. Hey, you're gonna help me
stain some chairs later, right?

08:07.500 --> 08:09.536
Dex gets mad
when I stain stuff.

08:09.540 --> 08:11.667
[ Chuckles ]
I could use your help,

08:11.670 --> 08:12.876
for real,
behind the bar tonight.

08:12.880 --> 08:14.416
All the beer you can drink.

08:14.420 --> 08:16.411
Well, I think we both know I'm
not exactly steady job material.

08:16.420 --> 08:18.741
I'd probably just mess up.

08:18.750 --> 08:20.661
And then I'd have to fire you
in front of your brother.

08:20.670 --> 08:23.286
Things would get awloNard.
Total resentment kicked in.

08:23.290 --> 08:24.609
But I will take you up
on the "all the free beer

08:24.620 --> 08:26.167
I can drink" part.
I'm really good at that.

08:26.170 --> 08:27.285
Look at us.
[ Chuckles ]

08:27.290 --> 08:29.076
We just saved a perfectly
good friendship.

08:29.080 --> 08:32.117
We're back.
Hey, thanks for your, um,
your help with Ansel.

08:32.120 --> 08:33.496
I owe you one.
Oh, stop it.

08:33.500 --> 08:34.489
I like him.
You know that.

08:35.960 --> 08:37.780
Alright, buddy,
I'm gonna take off.

08:37.790 --> 08:39.280
Love ya.
Love you, too, sis.

08:39.290 --> 08:40.826
-See ya.
-I miss you already.

08:40.830 --> 08:42.377
You too.

08:42.380 --> 08:46.532
[ Blondie's "Heart of Glass"
plays ]

08:46.540 --> 08:50.613
Once I had a love,
and it was a gas

08:50.620 --> 08:54.112
Soon turned out
had a heart of glass

08:54.120 --> 08:56.168
[ Music stops,
engine shuts off]

08:58.120 --> 08:59.166
Lucy Chen?

08:59.170 --> 09:01.661
I actually ordered
an Uber Select.

09:01.670 --> 09:03.114
I'm not your ride.

09:03.120 --> 09:05.532
Uh, Detective Parios,
Portland PB.

09:05.540 --> 09:08.202
I wanted to talk to you about
your friend, Nina Blackbird?

09:08.210 --> 09:10.667
Bull.

09:10.670 --> 09:13.241
Excuse me?
I call bull.

09:13.250 --> 09:16.208
Cops don't drive
piece-of-crap cars.

09:16.210 --> 09:18.417
Yeah, well, uh, you know,
I'm un-- I'm undercover.

09:18.420 --> 09:20.615
Then lemme see your badge.

09:20.620 --> 09:22.201
Okay.

09:22.210 --> 09:23.950
I'm working
for Nina's grandmother.

09:23.960 --> 09:26.531
I already told Hollis I haven't
talked to Nina in a week.

09:26.540 --> 09:28.167
So, if I check your phone,
I'm not gonna find

09:28.170 --> 09:30.912
anything from Nina?
No...calls or text messages?

09:30.920 --> 09:32.956
No.

09:32.960 --> 09:34.666
And even if they were
on my phone,

09:34.670 --> 09:36.035
I wouldn't give you
the password.

09:36.040 --> 09:38.611
So, it's, like, moot.

09:38.620 --> 09:41.612
Cool. Great.
Thank you so much.

09:41.620 --> 09:42.917
Mm.
You were so helpful.

09:42.920 --> 09:45.241
Mm-_hmm.
Really, this has been
invaluable.

09:45.250 --> 09:48.538
[ Car door opens, closes ]

09:48.540 --> 09:49.325
[ Engine sputters ]

09:49.330 --> 09:50.786
[ Sighs ]

09:54.710 --> 09:56.951
[ Engine sputters ]
Come on.

09:56.960 --> 09:58.530
[ Engine starts ]
[ Blondie's "Heart of Glass"
plays ]

09:58.540 --> 10:02.533
Seemed like the real thing,
only to find

10:02.540 --> 10:05.111
Mucho mistrust,
love's gone behind

10:09.330 --> 10:10.661
Answer.
Come on, answer, answer.

10:10.670 --> 10:11.876
Hey, it's Nina.

10:11.880 --> 10:12.744
Leave me a message.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

10:12.750 --> 10:14.240
Hey, it's me.

10:14.250 --> 10:16.377
Just give me a call
as soon as you can,

10:16.380 --> 10:18.029
and maybe send
your grandma a text

10:18.040 --> 10:18.995
and tell her that --

10:19.000 --> 10:19.876
Oop!

10:19.880 --> 10:21.245
What the hell
are you doing?

10:21.250 --> 10:22.820
Ha.
Give me my phone back.

10:22.830 --> 10:25.492
What do we have here?_
Some text messages from Nina.

10:25.500 --> 10:28.458
Give it back.
She's talking about a boy
named Michael.

10:28.460 --> 10:29.700
You don't happen to know
Michael's last name, do you?

10:29.710 --> 10:31.075
I'm not telling you squat.

10:31.080 --> 10:32.377
Is this Michael?

10:36.210 --> 10:37.780
Wait, Lucy,
are they going somewhere?

10:37.790 --> 10:39.576
[Jet engine humming ]

10:47.620 --> 10:48.951
[ Keys jingle ]

10:51.170 --> 10:52.410
[ Glass shatters ]

10:52.420 --> 10:54.035
[ Fire alarm ringing ]

10:54.040 --> 10:57.203
[ Indistinct talking ]

10:57.210 --> 11:00.077
Man: What the hell's going on?
Is there a fire?

11:00.080 --> 11:01.570
Don't worry about it!

11:05.500 --> 11:07.240
Room service.

11:09.710 --> 11:12.247
Um...we didn't
order anything.

11:12.250 --> 11:14.115
Oh,
this is more of a pick-up.

11:14.120 --> 11:15.701
Nina?

11:15.710 --> 11:18.577
Dex?
What are you doing here?

11:18.580 --> 11:20.286
Taking you home.
Yeah, well,
I'm calling the cops.

11:20.290 --> 11:21.370
Okay, sure.

11:21.380 --> 11:23.666
Uh, go ahead,
but, um...I'm pretty sure

11:23.670 --> 11:27.117
transporting a minor across
state lines in jailable.

11:27.120 --> 11:28.997
I bought the tickets.
We're eloping.

11:29.000 --> 11:30.615
Oh. Where's your ring?

11:32.460 --> 11:34.325
I'm saving up for it.

11:34.330 --> 11:35.615
Wow. What a catch.

11:35.620 --> 11:37.918
Okay, honeymoon is over.
Let's go.

11:41.040 --> 11:43.873
[ Windshield wipers squeak]
Ugh. Another one.

11:43.880 --> 11:45.609
[ Sighs ]

11:45.620 --> 11:48.032
[ Window whirs ]
I knew this
was gonna happen.

11:48.040 --> 11:51.282
Well, you wanna blame someone?
Blame Grandma.

11:51.290 --> 11:53.827
Don't you hate yourself
just a little,

11:53.830 --> 11:56.993
doing to me and Michael
what she did to you and my dad?

11:57.000 --> 11:58.160
And what does
that make you?

11:58.170 --> 12:00.491
Employed.
Hypocrite, is more like it.

12:00.500 --> 12:02.240
Hey, how about a little bit
of quiet time?

12:04.080 --> 12:05.616
What happened with you
and my dad,

12:05.620 --> 12:08.612
it's the whole reason
I'm doing this.

12:08.620 --> 12:11.498
I don't want it
to happen to me.

12:11.500 --> 12:13.070
[ Car engine revs ]

12:13.080 --> 12:14.991
[ Crash, tape deck clicks ]
Oh, geez. Seriously?

12:15.000 --> 12:17.036
Love

12:17.040 --> 12:19.497
Love will keep us together

12:19.500 --> 12:20.535
Your radio's broken.

12:20.540 --> 12:22.167
No, it's a mixtape.

12:22.170 --> 12:24.115
Cassette, okay?
It came with the car.

12:24.120 --> 12:25.667
Just don't antagonize it

12:25.670 --> 12:27.956
and it might go off on its own,
alright?

12:27.960 --> 12:29.666
...singing her song

12:29.670 --> 12:31.490
It's the perfect song, huh?

12:31.500 --> 12:35.243
You just got to be strong,
just stop

12:35.250 --> 12:36.410
'Cause I really love you...

12:36.420 --> 12:38.661
Just in case, alright?
Stop

12:38.670 --> 12:40.911
I'll be thinking of you

12:40.920 --> 12:42.660
Look in my heart...

12:42.670 --> 12:44.740
Well, lucky for you,
that dent matches the others.

12:44.750 --> 12:47.321
How about you --
[ Grunts ]

12:47.330 --> 12:48.786
[ Groans ]

12:48.790 --> 12:52.282
[ High-pitched ringing ]

12:52.290 --> 12:54.076
You
[ Grunts ]

12:54.080 --> 12:55.957
You belong...
Come on.

12:55.960 --> 12:58.531
Go!

12:58.540 --> 13:01.077
[ Breathing heavily ]

13:01.080 --> 13:02.115
Run!

13:02.120 --> 13:05.032
I will, I will, I will

13:05.040 --> 13:08.532
I will be there
to share forever
Dex! Dex!

13:08.540 --> 13:10.872
[ Grunts ]

13:10.880 --> 13:14.748
Love will keep us together

13:14.750 --> 13:18.208
I said it before
and I'll say it again
[ Gasps ]

13:18.210 --> 13:20.496
While others pretend
[ Grunting ]

13:20.500 --> 13:23.492
I need you now
and I'll need you then
Dex! Dex!

13:23.500 --> 13:25.161
Just stop
[ Grunts ]

13:25.170 --> 13:27.377
'Cause I really love you

13:27.380 --> 13:28.916
Stop

13:28.920 --> 13:31.115
I'll be thinking of you
[ Breathing heavily ]

13:31.120 --> 13:32.701
Look in my heart...
No!

13:32.710 --> 13:34.075
-Come on!
-Dex!

13:34.080 --> 13:36.287
...keep us together

13:36.290 --> 13:38.531
[ Grunting ]

13:38.540 --> 13:40.917
[ Seatbelt clicks ]

13:40.920 --> 13:42.785
I will, I will, I will
[ Grunting ]

13:42.790 --> 13:46.112
No!
Come on!

13:46.120 --> 13:48.372
[ Groans ]
Ba-ba-ba-ba

13:48.380 --> 13:51.611
Come on, Whale!
Dex, help me!

13:51.620 --> 13:53.110
[ Grunts ]
Come on!

13:53.120 --> 13:54.701
You gotta learn
when to quit, lady.

13:54.710 --> 13:56.575
Let's go, Whale!

13:56.580 --> 13:58.320
[ Engine starts ]
Dex, help!

13:58.330 --> 13:59.877
Dex, help!
Come on!

13:59.880 --> 14:01.108
Dex!

14:01.120 --> 14:04.704
Da-da-da-da

14:10.710 --> 14:12.166
[ Vehicle door closes ]

14:12.170 --> 14:13.569
Yeah, look,
they came out of nowhere.

14:13.580 --> 14:16.663
I have no idea what happened.

14:16.670 --> 14:19.286
[ Vehicle door closes ]
Sue Lynn?

14:19.290 --> 14:20.996
Sue Lynn.

14:21.000 --> 14:22.570
[ Police radio chatter ]

14:22.580 --> 14:24.912
[ Cellphone clicks ]
Miss Parios?

14:24.920 --> 14:28.208
Yeah.
Detective Hoffman, PPB.

14:28.210 --> 14:30.110
Can you tell me
what happened here, ma'am?

14:30.120 --> 14:32.827
[ Sighs ] Listen, I already told
two other cops the whole story,

14:32.830 --> 14:33.990
so I don't really feel like
I need to get into it.

14:34.000 --> 14:35.991
Okay, but th-- the thing is,
see, kidnapping

14:36.000 --> 14:37.570
is pretty serious business,
so you'll probably...

14:37.580 --> 14:39.821
Mm-hmm.
...have to tell a few more
of us down at the station.

14:39.830 --> 14:42.572
Nah, I don't think so.
[ Sighs ]

14:42.580 --> 14:45.117
Excuse me?
As long as she's out there,
I need to be looking for her.

14:45.120 --> 14:47.827
The station is up, FYI,
not down.

14:47.830 --> 14:48.876
I don't know
why people say that.

14:51.000 --> 14:53.958
[ Clears through ]
Ma'am?

14:53.960 --> 14:55.700
Your vehicle.

14:55.710 --> 14:58.611
That's a fancy word for it.

14:58.620 --> 14:59.996
Don't call me ma'am.
Yeah?

15:00.000 --> 15:01.570
What would you like me
to call you?
Dex.

15:01.580 --> 15:02.877
Dex?
My name IS Dex.

15:02.880 --> 15:04.950
Very well, Dex.
I need to arrest you.

15:04.960 --> 15:06.700
[ Chuckles softly ] For what?
For getting beat up?

15:06.710 --> 15:08.871
For 14 unpaid
parking tickets.

15:08.880 --> 15:10.324
Apparently there's
a warrant out,

15:10.330 --> 15:13.458
so...we're gonna go up
to the station.

15:15.000 --> 15:17.616
[ Clock ticking rapidly ]

15:17.620 --> 15:18.951
[ Sighs ]

15:21.880 --> 15:23.916
Miss Parios.

15:23.920 --> 15:26.286
I'm Lieutenant Cosgrove.
Thanks for coming down.

15:26.290 --> 15:27.996
You can thank
Kauffman here.

15:28.000 --> 15:29.991
[ Exhales sharply]
Hoffman.

15:30.000 --> 15:32.537
Ma'am.
[ Chair scrapes along floor ]

15:32.540 --> 15:34.076
So, any word on Nina?

15:34.080 --> 15:36.116
We found the suspects' car.

15:36.120 --> 15:37.371
It was stolen about a week ago
out of Bend.

15:37.380 --> 15:38.529
If there's any prints --

15:38.540 --> 15:40.747
The boyfriend give you
anything useful?

15:40.750 --> 15:42.570
How do you know we talked
to the boyfriend?

15:42.580 --> 15:44.377
Well [chuckles] it's always
the first place you look.

15:44.380 --> 15:45.916
Since I've been sitting here
for two hours

15:45.920 --> 15:47.069
drinking Portland's
crappiest coffee,

15:47.080 --> 15:48.377
I figured that
you were out there --

15:48.380 --> 15:51.076
The boyfriend
said that you forced your way

15:51.080 --> 15:53.287
into the motel and took Nina
against her Will.

15:53.290 --> 15:55.531
She's 17. She's not allowed
to have her own will.

15:55.540 --> 15:58.612
How about we talk about
your connection to Nina?

15:58.620 --> 15:59.700
Sure.

15:59.710 --> 16:02.201
Um...for the third time,

16:02.210 --> 16:04.997
I dated her father, Benny,
in college.

16:05.000 --> 16:06.570
I still see the family
around the Casino.

16:06.580 --> 16:07.877
That relationship
with Benny --

16:07.880 --> 16:09.324
if you were to describe
how it ended...?

16:09.330 --> 16:10.786
Well, with him marrying
somebody else.

16:10.790 --> 16:12.496
So, not well.

16:12.500 --> 16:15.037
For you.

16:15.040 --> 16:16.667
You say that like
I'm a suspect.

16:16.670 --> 16:18.820
Everyone's a suspect
until we establish the facts.

16:18.830 --> 16:19.910
Is that in the cop manual?

16:21.460 --> 16:23.917
The kidnappers' vehicle
was spotted at the motel

16:23.920 --> 16:25.615
just as you were leaving.

16:25.620 --> 16:28.919
So, either you
led them to Nina,

16:28.920 --> 16:32.492
or you just happened
to get there first.

16:32.500 --> 16:34.115
Yeah.

16:34.120 --> 16:35.781
That's why people
call the police

16:35.790 --> 16:37.667
when something
like this happens.

16:37.670 --> 16:40.571
When you hire an amateur, you're
gonna get amateur mistakes.

16:42.580 --> 16:44.878
[ Bottle slides ]

16:46.790 --> 16:49.918
Hey. Did you do all this?
Alone?

16:49.920 --> 16:51.785
I also cleaned
the mirrors in the bathroom

16:51.790 --> 16:53.109
and ate a pickle sandwich.

16:53.120 --> 16:55.202
[ Chuckling ]
And a pickle sandwich?

16:55.210 --> 16:56.871
Thanks for doing this.
It looks great.

16:58.620 --> 17:00.781
[ Cellphone ringing
and buzzing ]

17:04.330 --> 17:06.241
Thanks for bailing me out.
Yeah, I'll add it to your tab.

17:06.250 --> 17:08.070
I get it, okay?
I messed up, Grey. Alright?

17:08.080 --> 17:09.707
Hey, you're just luclq
you didn't get killed.

17:09.710 --> 17:11.200
[ Sighs ] I need to talk
to Nina's boyfriend.

17:11.210 --> 17:12.279
He knows something.

17:12.290 --> 17:13.416
Didn't the cops
already question him?

17:13.420 --> 17:14.455
Well,
it's not about questions.

17:14.460 --> 17:15.825
It's about how you ask
the questions, okay?

17:15.830 --> 17:18.458
Okay, here's an idea, alright?
And call me crazy --

17:18.460 --> 17:20.246
[ Sighs ]
Why don't you let
the cops handle it?

17:20.250 --> 17:22.741
And just walk away?
I'm not gonna do that, okay?

17:22.750 --> 17:24.206
I need to find her.

17:24.210 --> 17:25.074
Okay.

17:25.080 --> 17:26.707
Dex.
Yeah?

17:26.710 --> 17:30.282
I'm, uh, sorry for the way that
Cosgrove went at you in there.

17:30.290 --> 17:32.611
We all want to see
a happy ending on this one.

17:32.620 --> 17:34.417
Yeah, I get it.
Good cop, bad cop.

17:34.420 --> 17:36.376
Uh, which one are you?

17:40.460 --> 17:42.246
Oh, I'm gonna go
with good cop.

17:42.250 --> 17:44.241
This is my friend, Grey.

17:44.250 --> 17:46.241
Yeah, I'm her ride,
which is out front.

17:46.250 --> 17:47.660
You ready?
Mm-hmm.

17:47.670 --> 17:49.877
[ Indistinct chatter ]

17:51.540 --> 17:53.076
Nina: Please, please, please,
please! Don't do this!

17:53.080 --> 17:54.616
My grandma,
she can give you --

17:54.620 --> 17:55.826
[ Muffled talking ]

17:59.920 --> 18:02.036
[ Muffled screams ]

18:05.290 --> 18:07.281
[ Breathing heavily ]

18:09.920 --> 18:13.071
Whale: Cheer up, honey.
Things can always get worse.

18:18.250 --> 18:19.456
[ Neon sign buzzing ]

18:22.040 --> 18:25.077
The police
think I'm involved.

18:25.080 --> 18:27.116
Well, there's a lot of people
looking for Nina.

18:27.120 --> 18:28.576
Sue Lynn
is a powerful woman.

18:28.580 --> 18:30.207
That's why we had to leave.

18:30.210 --> 18:32.917
Guy like me -- no money,
I'm out of the bloodline.

18:32.920 --> 18:34.569
There was no way that I was ever
gonna be good enough

18:34.580 --> 18:36.241
for the family empire.

18:36.250 --> 18:38.536
I understand.
You ruined it.

18:38.540 --> 18:40.030
And saying sorry
won't fix it,

18:40.040 --> 18:41.610
but maybe I can make
things right, okay?

18:41.620 --> 18:43.827
Michael, if you know anything,
you need to tell me now.

18:46.040 --> 18:47.530
[ Sighs ]

18:49.000 --> 18:51.457
[ Exhales sharply]

18:51.460 --> 18:53.075
[ Inhales sharply ]

18:53.080 --> 18:54.320
You know, you wouldn't know it
to look at me,

18:54.330 --> 18:58.414
but I used to interrogate
people in the service.

18:58.420 --> 19:01.412
And I would get this feeling
when people were holding back,

19:01.420 --> 19:03.206
and I'm getting it now.

19:03.210 --> 19:04.780
Nina trusted you.

19:04.790 --> 19:07.202
She told you things you swore
never to tell anyone else.

19:07.210 --> 19:08.825
Then why
should I trust you?

19:08.830 --> 19:10.286
Because if something
happens to her,

19:10.290 --> 19:12.167
you're never gonna
forgive yourself.

19:12.170 --> 19:13.990
[ Insects chirping ]

19:17.040 --> 19:22.455
Sue Lynn...had business with
this gangster, Baxter Hall.

19:22.460 --> 19:25.532
When opioids starting showing up
on the reservation,

19:25.540 --> 19:29.169
she intercepted one of his
shipments and she torched it.

19:29.170 --> 19:31.877
So, Baxter's out
a ton of money.

19:31.880 --> 19:35.202
And maybe he's trying to get it
back from Sue Lynn another way.

19:35.210 --> 19:36.325
I wouldn't know
where to find him.

19:36.330 --> 19:38.116
Yeah,
I know somebody who might.

19:40.620 --> 19:42.417
_ _Hollis:
"Two million dollars, cash.

19:42.420 --> 19:44.115
If we see the police,
the next box will contain

19:44.120 --> 19:45.496
your granddaughter's
fingers.

19:45.500 --> 19:47.070
Expect instructions."

19:47.080 --> 19:48.661
Security found it
in a box outside.

19:48.670 --> 19:50.456
Looks like sawdust maybe?

19:50.460 --> 19:51.700
Blood?

19:53.210 --> 19:54.916
No, ma'am.

19:54.920 --> 19:57.115
Mrs. Blackbird, we're gonna need
to ask you a few questions.

19:57.120 --> 20:00.283
If I knew who was responsible,
Nina would be home already

20:00.290 --> 20:02.201
and you'd be counting
their fingers in a box.

20:02.210 --> 20:03.746
We would like to speak
to her parents.

20:03.750 --> 20:06.241
Nina's mother
is too distressed.
What about her father?

20:06.250 --> 20:08.992
He was killed in Afghanistan
serving his country.

20:09.000 --> 20:10.661
Sue Lynn speaks
for the family.

20:10.670 --> 20:11.705
[ Sighs ] Alright.

20:11.710 --> 20:13.325
We're gonna need to review

20:13.330 --> 20:15.958
all of the Casino footage,
monitor incoming calls...

20:15.960 --> 20:17.496
We need a list
of employees,

20:17.500 --> 20:19.115
business associates,
all of that.

20:19.120 --> 20:22.783
You'll include my people every
step of your investigation.

20:22.790 --> 20:26.669
[ Exhales sharply]
We're, uh, really accustomed
to operating independently.

20:26.670 --> 20:31.619
Yeah.
In here, you are guests
of the confederated tribes.

20:31.620 --> 20:35.613
We look forward to working
hand in hand...for once.

20:39.000 --> 20:40.536
Mm.

20:42.000 --> 20:43.536
Es lo que tu quieres

20:43.540 --> 20:45.747
Aqui tenemos lo que le gusta
a toda las mujeres

20:45.750 --> 20:48.571
Yo te hablo bonito pero
me comporto malo, baby

20:48.580 --> 20:50.616
[ Indistinct conversations ]
Te gusta lo latino
ya lo capto, baby

20:50.620 --> 20:52.997
You hear me talking crazy,
is 'cause you looking sew

20:53.000 --> 20:55.662
Hey, you need
a hand back there?

20:55.670 --> 20:56.955
[ Chuckles ]
Hey.

20:56.960 --> 20:58.530
No offense,
but you were the worst

20:58.540 --> 20:59.996
short-order cut
in Stumptown.

21:00.000 --> 21:01.319
Who puts mustard
on a taco?

21:01.330 --> 21:03.036
That was one time.
What happened to your face?

21:03.040 --> 21:04.109
What happened to your face?

21:05.620 --> 21:06.996
How's the taco trade?

21:07.000 --> 21:08.706
Complicated.
Oh, yeah?

21:08.710 --> 21:10.575
Back when you worked for me,
a taco was a taco.

21:10.580 --> 21:14.209
Now, all the competition,
social media...

21:14.210 --> 21:16.826
It's like every taquito needs
to win a Michelin star.

21:16.830 --> 21:18.878
Listen, Tookie,
I need your help.

21:18.880 --> 21:21.451
I need to find
Baxter Hall.

21:21.460 --> 21:23.451
How would I know
where he is?

21:23.460 --> 21:26.668
C'mon. 20 years,
rolling around in that tin can.

21:26.670 --> 21:28.535
I mean, nobody knows
the city like you.

21:28.540 --> 21:30.246
What can I say?
I'm outta the loop.
Yeah, you know what?

21:30.250 --> 21:34.414
Your eye...does this little
twitch when you're lying.

21:34.420 --> 21:35.956
Like when you tell
your customers

21:35.960 --> 21:37.496
that your chicken's
free-range.

21:37.500 --> 21:38.819
I only use organic.

21:38.830 --> 21:40.240
There it is.
Right there.

21:40.250 --> 21:42.036
We both know you buy
everything on the cheap.

21:42.040 --> 21:44.326
Hey, hey.
Keep it down.

21:44.330 --> 21:47.572
Someone hears you
and it's death by Yelp.

21:47.580 --> 21:49.457
Baxter's bad news, Dex.

21:49.460 --> 21:51.280
Well, he may have taken
something I need.

21:51.290 --> 21:52.826
Then let him have it.
That's not an option.

21:55.420 --> 21:57.240
Alright.

21:57.250 --> 21:59.536
Last I heard --
but on your life,

21:59.540 --> 22:01.110
you didn't hear it
from me...

22:01.120 --> 22:04.203
Mm-hmm?
...he was working out of the
Counter Culture in Old Town.

22:04.210 --> 22:06.166
Okay.

22:06.170 --> 22:07.819
Thanks, Took,
I owe you one.

22:07.830 --> 22:10.492
_ Don't thank me.
Hit me on Instagram.
I need the likes.

22:10.500 --> 22:13.037
[ Indistinct chatter,
siren wailing in distance ]

22:17.500 --> 22:19.991
Dex.
Long time.

22:20.000 --> 22:22.286
Hey.
You're working here now.

22:22.290 --> 22:23.450
Yeah, you never called me
after that night.

22:23.460 --> 22:25.416
I...thought
we hit it off.

22:25.420 --> 22:27.411
We slept together, though,
didn't we, Ted?

22:27.420 --> 22:29.411
Todd.
R-Right. My bad.

22:29.420 --> 22:30.739
Yeah. Sorry.

22:30.750 --> 22:34.823
So, um...are you gonna
let me in or not?

22:34.830 --> 22:36.536
Eh.
Cool, thanks.

22:36.540 --> 22:37.916
[ Scoffs ]

22:37.920 --> 22:39.706
Careful, don't drown

22:39.710 --> 22:41.610
Homie be playing,
I guess he a clown

22:41.620 --> 22:43.576
Ain't seen me yet
but obsessed with the sound

22:43.580 --> 22:45.411
Got on my Ray-Bans,
not messing around

22:45.420 --> 22:47.490
Make yo...hit the road, jack,
water into wine

22:47.500 --> 22:49.707
But I will sip the cognac,
sweet like a lollipop

22:49.710 --> 22:51.280
Hey, uh, I'm here
to see Baxter Hall.

22:51.290 --> 22:53.201
This ain't Bojack

22:53.210 --> 22:55.371
Not on no fake...
flows like oasis

22:55.380 --> 22:57.166
Both eyes wide open,
they ready for LASIK

22:57.170 --> 22:59.377
I run this like Asics,
I'm shining like braces

22:59.380 --> 23:00.574
Too slick when I slide,
all these...is basic

23:00.580 --> 23:02.377
Alright, yeah.

23:02.380 --> 23:03.916
Baxter Hall?

23:03.920 --> 23:05.569
What happened to your face?

23:05.580 --> 23:07.536
Oh. Yeah. Uh...

23:07.540 --> 23:09.997
I don't care.

23:10.000 --> 23:12.742
Did you bring the money?

23:12.750 --> 23:14.286
Yeah.

23:14.290 --> 23:16.611
Yeah, the, uh,
the money is, um, nearby,

23:16.620 --> 23:19.703
but I'm gonna have
to see the girl first.

23:19.710 --> 23:21.496
Girl is nearby.

23:21.500 --> 23:24.708
But I'm gonna need
some assurances first.

23:24.710 --> 23:27.998
Are you a cop?
No.

23:28.000 --> 23:30.571
It's just -- that's what a cop
would say, you know?

23:30.580 --> 23:33.538
So, I'm gonna have
to check for a wire.

23:33.540 --> 23:35.110
Well, it's a good thing
I wore my second-best bra.

23:36.670 --> 23:38.786
That's hilarious.

23:38.790 --> 23:41.918
Did you guys hear the thing
about the second-best bra?

23:41.920 --> 23:44.536
'Cause it's her
second-best bra.

23:44.540 --> 23:46.167
Okay.
Okay.

23:47.460 --> 23:49.200
You know, there's a lot of
people looking for the girl.

23:49.210 --> 23:50.450
It was not easy
getting her here.

23:50.460 --> 23:52.075
I bet she put up a ï¬ght,
too.

23:52.080 --> 23:53.911
Eh, not really.
It was lousy security.

23:53.920 --> 23:56.536
It was practically
a milk run.

23:56.540 --> 23:58.280
Okay, so, where is she?

23:58.290 --> 23:59.575
[ Claps hands ]

23:59.580 --> 24:02.162
Funny. [ Chuckles ]

24:02.170 --> 24:07.415
1970 GTO.
GOAT ragtop.

24:07.420 --> 24:09.240
Oh, so rare.

24:09.250 --> 24:12.037
Ain't she gorgeous?

24:12.040 --> 24:13.826
Yeah, I mean, look --
look at the -- look at her.

24:13.830 --> 24:14.706
Wow.
Right?

24:14.710 --> 24:16.371
Okay, well, let's, uh,

24:16.380 --> 24:18.200
do your little
inspection thingy

24:18.210 --> 24:20.701
and then we'll go
and count the money.

24:20.710 --> 24:24.248
Yeah. Cool.

24:24.250 --> 24:27.208
Um...Yeah, I'll just take
a little, uh, peekaroo.

24:27.210 --> 24:29.417
Yeah. Do your thing.

24:29.420 --> 24:32.241
Ooh.
Oh, she is nice.

24:32.250 --> 24:34.377
Got all the features
that you asked for, my man.

24:34.380 --> 24:35.745
Real nice.

24:39.380 --> 24:41.371
Uh, hey, you mind
ifI listen to her purr?

24:41.380 --> 24:42.950
Be my guest.
It's your hundred K.

24:42.960 --> 24:44.166
Right.

24:44.170 --> 24:46.491
Let's see
what she has to say, huh?

24:46.500 --> 24:47.785
[ Engine starts ]
Yeah.

24:47.790 --> 24:49.371
Whoo.
Ooh.

24:49.380 --> 24:51.666
Baxter Hall?

24:51.670 --> 24:53.285
Uh...
Sure. Yeah. Go ahead.

24:56.460 --> 24:59.577
Who are you?
I'm your buyer.

24:59.580 --> 25:01.662
Why is that woman
in my vehicle?

25:03.210 --> 25:05.826
[ Engine revs ]

25:05.830 --> 25:07.570
Don't shoot!

25:07.580 --> 25:10.913
[Tires squeal ]

25:10.920 --> 25:12.535
[ Groans ]

25:12.540 --> 25:14.826
[ Engine revs ]

25:22.330 --> 25:24.491
Somebody tell me that
that didn't just happen.

25:27.460 --> 25:28.609
Anybody!

25:28.620 --> 25:29.609
[ Exhales sharply]

25:29.620 --> 25:31.451
[ Cellphone rings ]

25:31.460 --> 25:32.745
[ Cellphone buzzes ]
Hey.

25:32.750 --> 25:34.160
Hey, it's Hoffman.

25:34.170 --> 25:35.319
I've been trying
to get ahold of you.

25:35.330 --> 25:39.369
_ Good news.
Nina's been returned.

25:39.380 --> 25:40.745
Wait, she what?

25:40.750 --> 25:42.661
She's back
with her family.

25:42.670 --> 25:44.376
Why don't you come down
to the station tomorrow

25:44.380 --> 25:45.369
and talk about it?

25:45.380 --> 25:46.699
[ Sighs ]

25:54.420 --> 25:56.536
[ Engine shuts off ]

25:56.540 --> 25:58.496
Keep it.

26:02.080 --> 26:03.377
Dropped her off
a mile down the road.

26:03.380 --> 26:05.666
Not a hair out of place.
Well, Nina's sharp.

26:05.670 --> 26:08.241
I'm sure she gave the police
enough to catch those guys.

26:08.250 --> 26:09.990
Yes, it's only
a matter of time.

26:10.000 --> 26:11.570
[ Sighs ]

26:11.580 --> 26:12.911
[ Exhales sharply]

26:15.790 --> 26:18.452
[ Door closes ]
Uh, listen,
I don't know what happened.

26:18.460 --> 26:20.166
[ Clears throat ] I'd like
to talk to Nina in person.

26:20.170 --> 26:21.819
She's with her mother.

26:21.830 --> 26:24.708
Maybe now
is not the best time.

26:24.710 --> 26:26.530
I hear rumors of an incident

26:26.540 --> 26:29.077
involving our ex-associate
Baxter Hall

26:29.080 --> 26:31.822
_ _ and a woman _
fitting your description.

26:31.830 --> 26:34.663
Yeah, I was, um, trying to do
the right thing.

26:34.670 --> 26:38.071
When I was a child,
there was a snow storm.

26:38.080 --> 26:40.457
A man came out
to fix the chimney.

26:40.460 --> 26:43.827
A plumber.
He was all we could find.

26:43.830 --> 26:47.379
But before he was finished,
he fell through the roof,

26:47.380 --> 26:51.032
leaving us completely exposed
with no chimney.

26:53.170 --> 26:54.819
I certainly hope
you haven't escalated

26:54.830 --> 26:58.288
our troubles with Baxter.

26:58.290 --> 27:00.167
The advance you gave me --
keeping it wouldn't be right.

27:00.170 --> 27:02.957
That won't be necessary.
It was my mistake.

27:02.960 --> 27:07.283
You don't hire a plumber
to fix a chimney.

27:07.290 --> 27:09.281
Nina's suffered enough
because of you.

27:18.080 --> 27:19.536
[ Door opens, slams ]

27:19.540 --> 27:20.871
[ Car horn blares ]

27:22.790 --> 27:24.280
[ Sighs ]

27:27.960 --> 27:30.110
[ Car hits bump,
tape deck clicks ]

27:30.120 --> 27:32.372
I think we're alone now

27:32.380 --> 27:36.828
There doesn't seem to be
anyone around

27:36.830 --> 27:39.822
I think we're alone now

27:39.830 --> 27:43.038
The beating of our hearts
is the only sound

27:44.580 --> 27:46.411
[ High-pitched ringing ]

27:51.710 --> 27:55.328
[ Echoing ]
Look at the way

27:55.330 --> 27:57.821
We gotta...
Hey, Mark, it's Dex.

27:57.830 --> 27:59.206
I'm back in town
just for the night.

27:59.210 --> 28:00.780
I was wondering
maybe if we could meet up.

28:00.790 --> 28:02.326
Maybe I could come over
to your place.

28:02.330 --> 28:03.877
[ Dial tone ]
Uh, it's Dex. It's Dex.

28:03.880 --> 28:06.417
I'd love to see you.
In town for the night...

28:06.420 --> 28:07.876
Hey, Sarah. I was wondering
if maybe I could come over...

28:07.880 --> 28:09.529
Well, you know, maybe I could
come over...

28:09.540 --> 28:10.996
...grab a drink...
...and we could meet up
or something.

28:11.000 --> 28:11.989
Maybe I could come over
just for the night.

28:17.380 --> 28:19.029
Medic!

28:20.380 --> 28:22.666
Hey, um...

28:22.670 --> 28:23.785
Uh, listen, I need to talk.

28:23.790 --> 28:25.576
Um, you around?

28:25.580 --> 28:27.241
...alone now

28:27.250 --> 28:30.071
The beating of our hearts
is the only sound

28:35.960 --> 28:37.166
This couldn't wait
'til tomorrow?

28:41.540 --> 28:43.076
[ Moans ]

28:45.040 --> 28:47.417
What are we doing here,
Dex?

28:47.420 --> 28:49.115
Having fun.

28:49.120 --> 28:50.496
Mm.

28:50.500 --> 28:52.536
[ Breathing heavily ]

28:59.920 --> 29:01.114
You want something
to drink?

29:01.120 --> 29:02.701
No, I'm fine.
Thanks.

29:02.710 --> 29:04.280
I make a mean cup of tea.

29:04.290 --> 29:06.827
No, I actually have something
I have to do, so...

29:06.830 --> 29:07.910
At 2:00 in the morning?

29:07.920 --> 29:09.569
Wow.
Is it 2:00 already?

29:09.580 --> 29:11.207
Where has the time gone?

29:14.500 --> 29:16.206
Warmer.

29:18.710 --> 29:20.575
Warmer.

29:20.580 --> 29:22.377
Hot.

29:22.380 --> 29:23.779
Very hot.

29:26.670 --> 29:28.570
Post-its are a tad creepy.

29:28.580 --> 29:30.787
They help me track leads
and mysteries.

29:30.790 --> 29:31.779
I like a good mystery.

29:34.670 --> 29:37.070
Well, here's one
that I've been working on.

29:37.080 --> 29:39.287
Subject's marriage
falls apart.

29:39.290 --> 29:43.283
Despite having a cushy job
in the family business,

29:43.290 --> 29:47.954
he joins the Army
and deploys to Afghanistan.

29:47.960 --> 29:49.825
Six months into the tour,
he gets leave,

29:49.830 --> 29:51.411
but he doesn't go home.

29:51.420 --> 29:54.708
He goes to Kabul,
where his Humvee hits an IED,

29:54.710 --> 29:56.701
killing him instantly.

29:56.710 --> 29:59.531
Personal effects
for a Benjamin Blackburn.

29:59.540 --> 30:03.658
Items found on the deceased --
$86 in cash

30:03.670 --> 30:06.241
and one diamond
engagement ring.

30:10.000 --> 30:13.322
You were the reason Benny
was there, Dex.

30:13.330 --> 30:15.161
Maybe you thought
saving Nina

30:15.170 --> 30:17.320
would somehow make up
for losing him.

30:17.330 --> 30:18.410
[ Clears throat ]

30:20.290 --> 30:23.578
Wow. You put that together
all on your own?

30:23.580 --> 30:25.286
We had to know
how you fit in.

30:28.170 --> 30:29.660
[ Sighs ]

30:34.330 --> 30:35.376
What are these?

30:35.380 --> 30:36.529
We think they may
have kept Nina

30:36.540 --> 30:37.780
at a construction site.

30:37.790 --> 30:38.870
What did Nina say?

30:38.880 --> 30:40.165
Sue Lynn
won't let us near her.

30:40.170 --> 30:42.286
Wait, what? She's --
Why would she do that?

30:42.290 --> 30:43.826
I mean, these people
kidnapped her granddaughter.

30:43.830 --> 30:45.912
Apparently, these guys,
they just dropped her off

30:45.920 --> 30:46.909
right in front
of the Casino.

30:46.920 --> 30:48.990
No, Hollis told me
that she was

30:49.000 --> 30:50.456
dropped off
a mile down the road.

30:50.460 --> 30:51.779
Those are conflicting
stories.

30:51.790 --> 30:53.530
Look, we had to kick
this up to the Feds.

30:53.540 --> 30:55.201
You just passed this along?

30:55.210 --> 30:57.917
They have jurisdiction
where we don't.

30:57.920 --> 31:00.036
It's out of my hands.
[ Scoffs ]

31:00.040 --> 31:00.950
And yours.

31:03.750 --> 31:04.819
Yeah, not this time.

31:08.620 --> 31:11.032
[ Siren wailing ]

31:13.330 --> 31:14.740
Uh, Nina's back.

31:14.750 --> 31:17.708
Oh, that's great.
Yeah.

31:17.710 --> 31:21.032
I still think that, uh, Sue Lynn
is hiding something, though.

31:21.040 --> 31:23.668
Your brother's asleep
in the back office.

31:23.670 --> 31:25.615
Yeah.
I should have called.

31:25.620 --> 31:27.167
[ Clears throat ]

31:29.880 --> 31:31.609
What?
Someone you know?

31:31.620 --> 31:32.780
Or a one-night stand again?

31:32.790 --> 31:35.031
Oh, come on, man. What are you?
My dad?

31:35.040 --> 31:36.917
This is so --
I'm not your dad.
I'm your friend.

31:36.920 --> 31:38.660
Well, friends don't judge.

31:38.670 --> 31:40.285
Yeah,
friends tell the truth.

31:40.290 --> 31:42.372
Probably time you
start figuring out
this PTSD, because --

31:42.380 --> 31:43.870
Grey, that's not
what this is about.
It might be what it's about.

31:43.880 --> 31:44.869
That's notN-- It's not --
0.
Yeah, but it might be.

31:44.880 --> 31:46.370
I know Sue Lynn, okay?
Okay.

31:46.380 --> 31:47.574
I know her.
Okay.

31:47.580 --> 31:49.377
She would want
those kidnappers strung up.

31:49.380 --> 31:51.280
W-Why wouldn't she let Nina
talk to the cops?

31:51.290 --> 31:52.609
I mean,
none of it makes any sense.

31:52.620 --> 31:54.201
Dex, you think you can do
five tours in Afghanistan

31:54.210 --> 31:55.199
and not be left with a dent?

31:55.210 --> 31:56.245
Look, no --
Without any damages?

31:56.250 --> 31:57.239
It's not the way
it works.

31:57.250 --> 31:58.535
What if --
What if Sue Lynn lied?

31:58.540 --> 32:01.111
What if she lied
so she could sideline the cops

32:01.120 --> 32:02.826
and handle
the ransom herself?

32:02.830 --> 32:05.412
Dex --
I mean, Nina could still be out
there somewhere, Grey.

32:05.420 --> 32:06.739
I mean,
there is something wrong here.

32:06.750 --> 32:08.490
With you!

32:13.040 --> 32:15.281
[ Sighs ]
Nina's home.

32:15.290 --> 32:16.575
So are you.

32:18.580 --> 32:19.990
It's time to move on.

32:20.000 --> 32:21.536
Mm-hmm.

32:28.580 --> 32:30.536
[ Bird caws ]

32:34.790 --> 32:35.870
Hey, buddy.

32:41.120 --> 32:42.451
I miss Benny.

32:42.460 --> 32:46.669
He was always nice to me
and knew lots of funny jokes.

32:46.670 --> 32:49.537
I miss him, too.

32:49.540 --> 32:53.374
Dex, when I get sad,
I go to a park

32:53.380 --> 32:57.032
and I kick the ball
and pretend I win a game.

32:57.040 --> 33:00.112
I always feel better.

33:00.120 --> 33:01.826
Yeah.

33:04.540 --> 33:06.872
You know what? Why don't you
go get your ball, buddy, okay?

33:06.880 --> 33:08.495
You go to the park.

33:09.620 --> 33:10.996
Oh.

33:11.000 --> 33:12.319
Thanks.

33:22.290 --> 33:24.451
You know, we're gonna
make a stop first.

33:24.460 --> 33:26.917
I could use a win.

33:28.330 --> 33:30.537
Hold me tight

33:30.540 --> 33:32.952
Hey

33:32.960 --> 33:34.530
Tonight you -- Hey -- me

33:34.540 --> 33:36.451
Alright, buddy.

33:36.460 --> 33:38.781
Um, look, you can play
a few games.

33:38.790 --> 33:39.779
Just be a minute, okay?

33:39.790 --> 33:42.452
Okay.

33:42.460 --> 33:44.280
It's alright

33:44.290 --> 33:46.952
So, um, Nina's back home.

33:46.960 --> 33:49.201
I heard.

33:49.210 --> 33:51.030
You said you were saving up
for one, so...

33:58.710 --> 34:00.496
You know, the guy who was gonna
give me that?

34:00.500 --> 34:02.707
He, uh...
[ Clears throat ]

34:02.710 --> 34:05.452
He let some people
talk him out of it.

34:05.460 --> 34:09.908
And by the time he listened
to himself, it was too late.

34:09.920 --> 34:11.660
I don't know what to say.

34:11.670 --> 34:14.662
Well, uh, say you won't make
the same mistake he did.

34:28.420 --> 34:31.162
Michael...

34:31.170 --> 34:32.910
Michael,
what have you done with Nina?

34:34.080 --> 34:35.206
[ Grunts ]

34:35.210 --> 34:37.075
[ Groans ]
What do we do?

34:37.080 --> 34:39.116
Hand your little girlfriend
to Grandma

34:39.120 --> 34:40.747
and get our money.

34:46.750 --> 34:48.115
[ Car door opens, closes ]

34:48.120 --> 34:50.452
[ Engine revs, tires squeal ]

35:02.170 --> 35:03.706
[ Cellphone rings, buzzes ]

35:06.460 --> 35:08.166
Hey, what's up?
Ansel: De-- De-- De-- De--

35:08.170 --> 35:09.239
Ansel, you okay?

35:09.250 --> 35:10.615
Dex left without me.

35:10.620 --> 35:11.917
What does that mean?
Where did she go?

35:11.920 --> 35:13.114
Where did Dex go?

35:13.120 --> 35:14.667
I don't know.
She wasn't driving.

35:14.670 --> 35:15.989
Just hold tight, okay?

35:22.330 --> 35:24.412
Something might have happened
to Dex, okay?

35:24.420 --> 35:25.990
Two guys left in her car.

35:26.000 --> 35:26.876
Sh-- She might
have been kidnapped.

35:26.880 --> 35:29.496
Hold on.

35:29.500 --> 35:32.958
All units, be on the lookout
for an orange '92 Mustang GT.

35:32.960 --> 35:34.325
Possible abduction.

35:34.330 --> 35:37.117
Whale: ...it's tart
but has an earthy finish.

35:37.120 --> 35:38.576
[ Breathing heavily ]

35:38.580 --> 35:39.911
I'm going with Ethiopian.

35:39.920 --> 35:41.660
Dill: Ha! Kenyan.
[ Pounding ]

35:41.670 --> 35:43.410
Hey!
Sounds like somebody's getting
a little nervous back there.

35:43.420 --> 35:44.819
Let me out of here!

35:44.830 --> 35:46.570
Sue Lynn: The police
think Nina's home.

35:46.580 --> 35:47.990
I've held up my end.

35:48.000 --> 35:49.410
Now you better hold up yours.

35:53.580 --> 35:56.959
[ Grunting ]

35:56.960 --> 35:58.416
[ Breathing heavily ]

36:00.830 --> 36:04.414
Then spring became
the summer

36:04.420 --> 36:08.413
Both: Who'd have believed
you'd come along?

36:10.750 --> 36:12.240
Hands

36:12.250 --> 36:13.535
[ Fire extinguisher hisses ]

36:13.540 --> 36:15.280
[ Coughs ]

36:15.290 --> 36:16.780
Touching hands
[Tires squeal ]

36:16.790 --> 36:18.530
[ Car horn blares ]

36:18.540 --> 36:19.279
[ Glass shatters ]

36:19.290 --> 36:22.498
Reaching out

36:22.500 --> 36:23.956
Touching me
Car!

36:23.960 --> 36:24.995
[ Screams ]
[ Car horn blares ]

36:25.000 --> 36:26.570
Touching you

36:26.580 --> 36:28.457
[ Screams ]

36:28.460 --> 36:29.745
[ Screams ]

36:29.750 --> 36:32.457
Sweet Caroline

36:34.580 --> 36:37.492
Good times never
seemed so good

36:37.500 --> 36:40.822
[Tires squeal ]

36:40.830 --> 36:43.458
I've been inclined

36:45.580 --> 36:46.820
To believe
[ Coughs ]

36:46.830 --> 36:49.822
There never would

36:49.830 --> 36:50.819
[ Exhales sharply]

36:50.830 --> 36:51.876
[ Grunts ]
[ Coughs ]

36:51.880 --> 36:54.280
Sweet Caroline

36:54.290 --> 36:56.918
[ Grunts ]
[ Screams ]

36:56.920 --> 36:59.070
Good times
never seemed so good
[ Grunts ]

37:02.170 --> 37:03.034
[ Gun cocks ]

37:03.040 --> 37:04.246
Where is she?

37:04.250 --> 37:06.912
[ Panting ]

37:08.880 --> 37:10.700
Michael!
Michael, we have to go!

37:10.710 --> 37:12.871
We have to go
before they come back!

37:13.790 --> 37:14.575
[ Exhales sharply]

37:26.670 --> 37:28.490
[ Engine revs ]

37:28.500 --> 37:29.819
[ Car rumbles over train track,
tape deck clicks ]

37:29.830 --> 37:32.116
[The O'Jays'
"Love Train" plays ]

37:32.120 --> 37:34.372
[ Police siren blares ]

37:36.380 --> 37:38.666
People all over the world
Come on!

37:38.670 --> 37:40.911
We were just kidding around!

37:40.920 --> 37:44.117
Start a love train,
love train

37:44.120 --> 37:46.111
People all over the world

37:46.120 --> 37:47.451
Dispatch: All units,
orange Mustang GT

37:47.460 --> 37:48.825
spotted heading east on Alder.

37:48.830 --> 37:50.240
Unit 2510 responding.

37:50.250 --> 37:52.320
[ Engine starts, siren blaring ]

37:54.580 --> 37:56.411
[Tires squeal ]

38:02.830 --> 38:05.458
I'll take my granddaughter
home now, thank you.

38:05.460 --> 38:07.280
Ama!

38:07.290 --> 38:08.700
...love train

38:08.710 --> 38:10.917
People all over the world

38:10.920 --> 38:12.785
Join hands

38:12.790 --> 38:14.109
Start a love train

38:14.120 --> 38:15.451
Alright
Love train

38:15.460 --> 38:16.950
[ Gun cocks ]

38:19.080 --> 38:21.742
Stupid boy.

38:21.750 --> 38:24.162
[ Sirens approaching ]

38:24.170 --> 38:25.819
[ Car stereo blaring
in distance ]

38:28.460 --> 38:33.033
Tell all the folks in Russia
and China, too

38:36.670 --> 38:42.324
Don't you know that it's time
to get on board?

38:42.330 --> 38:43.877
[ Grunts ]

38:43.880 --> 38:51.958
And let this train keep
on riding, riding on through

38:51.960 --> 38:53.279
People all over the world

38:53.290 --> 38:54.416
You don't need no money
[ Grunts ]

38:54.420 --> 38:56.240
Join hands
Come on

38:56.250 --> 38:58.878
Don't shoot, don't shoot
Love train

38:58.880 --> 39:00.871
We got it from here, Dex.

39:00.880 --> 39:02.416
[ Sighs ]
You okay?

39:02.420 --> 39:04.115
Yeah.
[ Muffled screams ]

39:04.120 --> 39:05.371
There's two more
in the trunk.

39:05.380 --> 39:06.824
Come ooooon

39:06.830 --> 39:09.572
Get on board

39:09.580 --> 39:11.457
[ Police radio chatter ]

39:14.750 --> 39:16.706
Hey.

39:16.710 --> 39:18.826
Hey, how you doing?

39:18.830 --> 39:20.115
[ Vehicle door closes ]

39:20.120 --> 39:21.610
Look, Nina,
I'm really sorry.

39:21.620 --> 39:23.531
Are you kidding?

39:23.540 --> 39:26.111
You saved my life.

39:26.120 --> 39:29.374
I was...just doing my job.

39:29.380 --> 39:33.168
Suppose you might have been
the right person for it.

39:33.170 --> 39:35.877
Wow. You always were the master
of the non-apology apology.

39:37.960 --> 39:39.609
[ Chuckles softly ]

39:39.620 --> 39:41.076
[ Car door opens ]

39:47.250 --> 39:50.617
[ Sighs ]

39:50.620 --> 39:52.030
[ Keys jingle ]

39:55.290 --> 39:57.372
[ Engine sputtering ]

39:57.380 --> 39:59.530
[ Police radio chatter ]

40:03.960 --> 40:05.166
Fine.

40:05.170 --> 40:07.161
[ Engine sputters, starts ]

40:09.330 --> 40:11.457
[ Sighs ]

40:11.460 --> 40:12.916
Hey

40:15.420 --> 40:17.069
Grey: Take this out back,
okay?

40:17.080 --> 40:18.570
Okay. Trash.

40:18.580 --> 40:20.707
Thank you, man.

40:20.710 --> 40:22.450
Well, look at this.
Looks like I got a bar.

40:22.460 --> 40:24.371
Congrats.

40:24.380 --> 40:25.608
[ Glasses clink]

40:25.620 --> 40:27.576
And, uh...thank you.

40:27.580 --> 40:28.956
For what?

40:28.960 --> 40:31.451
Well, for...how you are
with Ansel,

40:31.460 --> 40:34.998
and...for always bailing me out,
calling me out on my crap.

40:35.000 --> 40:36.410
And for the free beer,
which you like.

40:36.420 --> 40:39.617
[ Sighs, chuckles ]
Yeah, for that most of all.

40:39.620 --> 40:41.781
It's...
You know, it's nothing.

40:41.790 --> 40:43.951
No, it's not.
It's...

40:43.960 --> 40:44.870
It's everything.

40:47.120 --> 40:49.748
Ma'am...

40:49.750 --> 40:50.819
Kauffman.

40:50.830 --> 40:52.161
[ Chuckles ]

40:52.170 --> 40:54.070
I, uh,
thought you might be here.

40:54.080 --> 40:56.662
I also thought, uh,
you might want this back.

40:56.670 --> 40:58.376
Oh, wowzer.

40:58.380 --> 40:59.870
You're not gonna get down
on one knee?

40:59.880 --> 41:01.700
[ Chuckles ] Nah.
Come on.

41:01.710 --> 41:02.779
No?
You don't want that.

41:02.790 --> 41:04.781
Thank you.

41:04.790 --> 41:07.418
So, listen, things could have
really gone bad with Nina,

41:07.420 --> 41:12.198
and they didn't 'cause of you,
so...thank you.

41:12.210 --> 41:13.700
Well, I'm gonna take that
as a compliment.

41:13.710 --> 41:15.166
You should.

41:15.170 --> 41:17.661
Um, I may regret
saying this,

41:17.670 --> 41:20.321
but sometimes people
have problems, alright?

41:20.330 --> 41:21.911
And they're
the kind of problems

41:21.920 --> 41:23.205
that police
can't help with.

41:23.210 --> 41:25.451
I got a friend
who's in that kind of jam.

41:25.460 --> 41:26.916
I think
he could use your help.

41:26.920 --> 41:28.990
He'll pay you.

41:29.000 --> 41:30.456
Yeah, cool.

41:30.460 --> 41:34.829
Alright. Look, if you're
interested, give him a call.

41:34.830 --> 41:36.570
Thanks.

41:36.580 --> 41:37.615
Pay your parking tickets,
Dex.

41:37.620 --> 41:39.247
[ Chuckles ]

41:39.250 --> 41:42.071
I don't want to have
to arrest you again.

41:42.080 --> 41:43.991
You kinda want to,
though, a little bit.

41:49.830 --> 41:50.956
What do you think?
Should I call?

41:50.960 --> 41:52.200
No, I don't think
you should call.

41:52.210 --> 41:54.030
You can barely find
your keys half the time.

41:54.040 --> 41:55.200
He said it would pay.

41:55.210 --> 41:56.746
Are you honestly
considering doing this?

41:56.750 --> 41:58.615
I don't know.

41:58.620 --> 42:01.453
Might keep me
out of trouble.

42:01.460 --> 42:04.327
It might.
There he is.

42:04.330 --> 42:07.493
Hey, buddy.
I got your water ready.

42:07.500 --> 42:09.286
Cheers.
Cheers.

42:09.290 --> 42:10.530
Cheers.

42:10.540 --> 42:14.203
Come on and think,
think about you

42:14.210 --> 42:17.748
Come on and think
about the good things

